## About The Project

[![Product Name Screen Shot][product-screenshot]](https://example.com)

<br />

  <ul>
    <li>Assembled the back end of a movie website allowing any user to search for their favorite movies. </li>
    <li>Used CRUD methods for reviews, and view theaters and movies that are showing.</li>
    <li>Applied router and controller functions to retrieve a users's specific requests. </li>
  </ul>

<!-- GETTING STARTED -->
## Getting Started

### Do this first:

* Create and connect a DB:


*  Clone the front end and follow the instructions to get it running. 
  ```sh
git clone https://github.com/Samantha-Source/starter-movie-front-end.git
  ```



### Installation

1. Clone the repo
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/samantha-source/WeLoveMovies.git
   ```
2. Install NPM packages
   ```sh
   npm install
   ```
3. Create and connect a Data Base
  * You can do so for free here: [ElephanSQL](https://www.elephantsql.com/)
  * Create a .env file in the project folder:
    ```sh
      DATABASE_URL = "<Your_data_base_url>"
    ```
4. Run
   ```sh
   npm start
   ```
